What is a Factorial?
The factorial of a non-negative integer  n  is the product of all positive integers less than or equal to  n . It is denoted mathematically as  n!  and can be calculated using the following formulas:

 0! = 1

N! = N  (N-1) * (N-2)... for N > 0.


Example:
 5! = 5 \times 4 \times 3 \times 2 \times 1 = 120 

